President Donald J. Trump met with Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov to discuss several issues. Trump emphasized the importance of working together to end the conflict in Syria and urged Russia to rein in the Assad regime, Iran, and Iranian proxies. He also discussed Ukraine and expressed his commitment to resolving the conflict, highlighting Russia's responsibility to implement the Minsk agreements. Trump also mentioned the possibility of broader cooperation on resolving conflicts in the Middle East and elsewhere, and expressed his desire to improve the relationship between the United States and Russia.